The paper discusses the development of a prediction model using machine learning algorithms for travel time on freeways. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Basic Safety Messages (BSM) for data collection and processing involves communication and information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The evaluation of the prediction model involves comparing different tree-based ensemble algorithms, which falls under computational engineering (cs.CE).
